  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "These values are then integrated using a late fusion technique to recognize interactions.",
    "According to Wang,Huang,and Zhang [23], relying just on appearance data is insufficient for accurately representing complex human-object interactions, which makes the late fusion approach less than optimum.",
    "Furthermore, the pairwise stream merges the individual person and item boxes to create a reference box that is used to generate a binary image representation.",
    "Nevertheless, this methodology might provide inaccurate forecasts due to its dependence on restricted geographical data.",
    "Consistent with previous research [24,25], we use a Feature Pyramid Network (FPN) to provide predictions for bounding boxes of objects and humans."
  ],
